<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="224" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d224">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">121.893/3–746: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Truman</persName> to
                                General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-07">7 March 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>WH 410. Replying to your message dated 6 March you are hereby directed to
                            return to Washington for consultation.</p>
                        <p>In view of Mr. Churchill’s<note n="76" xml:id="d224fn76">Winston S.
                                Churchill, former British Prime Minister.</note> desire to see you
                            and in view of his departure from Washington on March 12 it is desired
                            that you arrive prior to 12 March if practicable.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Truman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>